<p><a name="Awards_and_honors" id="Awards_and_honors"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Gary_Gygax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Awards and honors">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Awards and honors</span></h2>
<p>Gygax received several awards and honors related to gaming, including the Academy of Adventure Gaming Arts &amp; Design <a href="/wiki/Origins_Award" title="Origins Award">Origins Award</a> Hall of Fame 1980.<sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34" title=""><span>[</span>35<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>Sync</i> Magazine named Gygax #1 on the list of "The 50 Biggest Nerds of All Time".<sup id="cite_ref-35" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-35" title=""><span>[</span>36<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>SFX</i> Magazine listed him as #37 on the list of the "50 Greatest <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">SF</a> Pioneers".<sup id="cite_ref-36" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-36" title=""><span>[</span>37<span>]</span></a></sup> In 1999 <i><a href="/wiki/Pyramid_(magazine)" title="Pyramid (magazine)">Pyramid</a></i> magazine named Gygax as one of <i>The Millennium's Most Influential Persons</i> "in the realm of adventure gaming."<sup id="cite_ref-37" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-37" title=""><span>[</span>38<span>]</span></a></sup> Gygax was tied with <a href="/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien" title="J. R. R. Tolkien">J. R. R. Tolkien</a> for #18 on GameSpy's 30 Most Influential People in Gaming.<sup id="cite_ref-38" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-38" title=""><span>[</span>39<span>]</span></a></sup> Numerous names in <i>Dungeons &amp; Dragons</i>, such as <a href="/wiki/Zagyg" title="Zagyg">Zagyg</a>, <i>Ring of Gaxx</i>, and Gryrax, are anagrams or alterations of Gygax's name.<sup id="cite_ref-39" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-39" title=""><span>[</span>40<span>]</span></a></sup> A strain of bacteria was also named in honor of Gygax, "<i>Arthronema gygaxiana sp nov UTCC393</i>".<sup id="cite_ref-40" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-40" title=""><span>[</span>41<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a href="/wiki/Blizzard_Entertainment" title="Blizzard Entertainment">Blizzard Entertainment</a> dedicated the 2.4.0 patch to <i><a href="/wiki/World_of_Warcraft" title="World of Warcraft">World of Warcraft</a></i>, "Fury of the Sunwell", to Gygax.<sup id="cite_ref-41" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-41" title=""><span>[</span>42<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Electronic_Arts" title="Electronic Arts">Electronic Arts</a> dedicated Publish 51 in <i><a href="/wiki/Ultima_Online" title="Ultima Online">Ultima Online</a></i> to Gygax. This included a new room in the dungeon Doom containing a special encounter and unique decorations.<sup id="cite_ref-42" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-42" title=""><span>[</span>43<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Turbine,_Inc." title="Turbine, Inc.">Turbine, Inc.</a> included two tributes in the <i><a href="/wiki/Dungeons_%26_Dragons_Online:_Stormreach" title="Dungeons &amp; Dragons Online: Stormreach">Dungeons &amp; Dragons Online: Stormreach</a></i> Module 7, released June 3 2008: A new area in Delera's Graveyard containing a memorial marker and text, and a new unique item, Voice of the Master, that improves the wearer's experience awards.<sup id="cite_ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43" title=""><span>[</span>44<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44" title=""><span>[</span>45<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a href="/wiki/Stephen_Colbert" title="Stephen Colbert">Stephen Colbert</a>, an avid <i>D&amp;D</i> gamer in his youth,<sup id="cite_ref-30_Years_19-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-30_Years-19" title=""><span>[</span>20<span>]</span></a></sup> dedicated the last part of the <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="03-05"><a href="/wiki/March_5" title="March 5">March 5</a></span>, 2008 episode of <a href="/wiki/The_Colbert_Report" title="The Colbert Report">The Colbert Report</a> to Gygax.<sup id="cite_ref-45" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-45" title=""><span>[</span>46<span>]</span></a></sup> Gygax was commemorated in a number of webcomics, including <a href="/wiki/Xkcd" title="Xkcd">xkcd</a>'s comic #393 "Ultimate Game,"<sup id="cite_ref-46" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-46" title=""><span>[</span>47<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Penny_Arcade_(webcomic)" title="Penny Arcade (webcomic)"><i>Penny Arcade'</i>s</a> "Bordering On The Semi-Tasteful,"<sup id="cite_ref-47" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-47" title=""><span>[</span>48<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Dork_Tower" title="Dork Tower"><i>Dork Tower</i></a>'s "Thanks for the Worldbuilding Rules,"<sup id="cite_ref-48" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-48" title=""><span>[</span>49<span>]</span></a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/Order_of_the_Stick" title="Order of the Stick" class="mw-redirect">Order of the Stick</a></i> #536,<sup id="cite_ref-49" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-49" title=""><span>[</span>50<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/UserFriendly" title="UserFriendly" class="mw-redirect">UserFriendly</a>'s Cartoon for March 9 2008<sup id="cite_ref-50" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-50" title=""><span>[</span>51<span>]</span></a></sup> and <a href="/wiki/GU_Comics" title="GU Comics">GU Comics</a>' "The Journey's End."<sup id="cite_ref-51" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-51" title=""><span>[</span>52<span>]</span></a></sup> The 2008 <i><a href="/wiki/Futurama" title="Futurama">Futurama</a></i> movie <i><a href="/wiki/Futurama:_Bender%27s_Game" title="Futurama: Bender's Game">Futurama: Bender's Game</a></i> is also dedicated to Gygax, with an animated clip of him from the episode "<a href="/wiki/Anthology_of_Interest" title="Anthology of Interest" class="mw-redirect">Anthology of Interest</a>" appearing after the credits.<sup id="cite_ref-52" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-52" title=""><span>[</span>53<span>]</span></a></sup> All three <i>Dungeons &amp; Dragons</i> 4th edition core rulebooks are also "dedicated to the memory of E. Gary Gygax."<sup id="cite_ref-53" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-53" title=""><span>[</span>54<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-54" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-54" title=""><span>[</span>55<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-55" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-55" title=""><span>[</span>56<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Gary_Gygax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
